[[Justin Timberlake]] is an American singer-songwriter, actor, dancer, and record producer. He is the recipient of 10 [[Grammy Award]]s, 4 [[Emmy Award]]s, 7 [[American Music Award]]s, 3 [[Brit Awards]], 9 [[Billboard Music Award|''Billboard'' Music Awards]], 11 [[MTV Video Music Award]]s and 29 [[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|ASCAP Awards]]. Overall, Timberlake has received 176 awards from 522 nominations {{as of|March 2020|lc=y}}.

His debut solo album, ''[[Justified (album)|Justified]]'', generated the singles "[[Like I Love You]]", "[[Rock Your Body]]", "[[Señorita (Justin Timberlake song)|Señorita]]", and the [[Grammy Award for Best Male Pop Vocal Performance]]-winning song "[[Cry Me a River (Justin Timberlake song)|Cry Me a River]]". Also nominated for [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]], it took home the [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album]]. Among other awards, it earned him [[American Music Awards]] for [[American Music Award for Favorite Pop/Rock Album|Favorite Pop/Rock Album]], [[Brit Awards]] for International Album and International Male, [[MTV Europe Music Awards]] for [[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Album|Best Album]] and [[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Male|Best Male]], and [[MTV Video Music Awards]] for [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Male Video|Best Male Video]] and [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Pop Video|Best Pop Video]]–the latter two for "Cry Me a River."

Timberlake's sophomore album ''[[FutureSex/LoveSounds]]'' garnered him seven Grammy nominations, including Album of the Year. Its singles "[[SexyBack]]" (in 2007) and "[[LoveStoned]]" (2008) both won [[Grammy Award for Best Dance Recording|Best Dance Recording]], while "[[My Love (Justin Timberlake song)|My Love]]" won [[Grammy Award for Best Rap/Sung Collaboration|Best Rap/Sung Collaboration]]. "[[What Goes Around... Comes Around]]" was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]] and won Best Male Pop Vocal Performance. The album won the American Music Awards for Favorite Pop/Rock Album and Favorite Soul/R&B Album.

Timberlake received the [[Michael Jackson Video Vanguard Award]] and won [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]] for "[[Mirrors (Justin Timberlake song)|Mirrors]]" at the [[2013 MTV Video Music Awards]]. He attended the [[2014 Billboard Music Awards|2014 ''Billboard'' Music Awards]] taking home seven awards, including [[Billboard Music Award for Top Artist|Top Artist]] and [[Billboard Music Award for Top Billboard 200 Album|Top Billboard 200 Album]] for ''[[The 20/20 Experience]]''. Timberlake earned seven Grammy nominations at the [[56th Annual Grammy Awards|2014 ceremony]], winning [[Grammy Award for Best Music Video|Best Music Video]] for "[[Suit & Tie]]", [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Song|Best R&B Song]] for "[[Pusher Love Girl]]", and Best Rap/Sung Collaboration for "[[Holy Grail (Jay Z song)|Holy Grail]]". For his third and fourth studio album he also won three [[American Music Award]]s and three [[People's Choice Awards]]. Timberlake was presented with the [[IHeartRadio Music Awards#iHeartRadio Innovator Award|Innovator Award]] at the [[2015 iHeartRadio Music Awards]]. In October 2015, he was inducted into the [[Memphis Music Hall of Fame]], becoming its youngest member.<ref name="mmhof">{{cite web|title=Justin Timberlake Sings Otis Redding, Gives Speech at Memphis Music Hall of Fame: Watch|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6731004/justin-timberlake-sings-otis-redding-memphis-music-hall-of-fame|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=October 18, 2015|accessdate=October 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Mehr|first=Bob|title=Justin Timberlake, Sam & Dave among Memphis Music Hall of Fame's class of 2015|url=http://www.commercialappeal.com/entertainment/music/justin-timberlake-sam--dave-among-memphis-music-hall-of-fames-class-of-2015-ep-1239822880-324100081.html|website=Commercial Appeal|date=August 21, 2015|accessdate=August 26, 2015}}</ref> He received the inaugural Decade Award at the [[2016 Teen Choice Awards]].<ref name="decade"/>

Timberlake has won four [[Emmy Award]]s, twice for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Original Music and Lyrics|Outstanding Original Music and Lyrics]] and twice for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series]]. Additionally, he has received two nominations for a [[Golden Globe Award for Best Original Song]]. In 2017, Timberlake received a nomination for an [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]] for "[[Can't Stop the Feeling!]]". In 2019, he received the [[Songwriters_Hall_of_Fame#Contemporary_Icon_Award|Contemporary Icon Award]] by the [[Songwriters Hall of Fame]].

