===Billboard.com Mid-Year Music Awards===
The Billboard.com Mid-Year Music Awards are held by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' to recognize the most favorite artists, songs, albums and performances of the first half of year. Winners are selected through a poll in ''Billboard'' official website. Justin Timberlake has been nominated seven times.

