==Emmy Awards==
The [[Emmy Award]], often referred to simply as the Emmy, is a television production award, similar in nature to the Peabody Awards but more focused on entertainment, and is considered the television equivalent to the Academy Awards (for film), Grammy Awards (for music), and the Tony Awards (for theatre). Justin Timberlake has received four awards from eight nominations.<ref>{{cite web|title=Justin Timberlake|url=http://www.emmys.com/bios/justin-timberlake|website=Television Academy - Emmy|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=M. Fernandez|first1=Sophia|title=Justin Timberlake Wins Two Emmy Awards for Work on 'Saturday Night Live'|url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/tv-film/1170206/justin-timberlake-wins-two-emmy-awards-for-work-on-saturday-night|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Vena|first1=Jocelyn|title=Lady Gaga, Eminem, Justin Timberlake Take Home Emmys|website=MTVnews.com|accessdate=26 July 2014|url = http://www.mtv.com/news/1670559/lady-gaga-emmys-justin-timberlake-eminem/}}</ref>

