==Grammy Awards==
The [[Grammy Award]]s are awarded annually by [[The Recording Academy]] of the United States for outstanding achievements in the [[music industry]]. Considered the highest music honor, the awards were established in 1958. Justin Timberlake has won 10 awards out of 39 nominations. His wins include categories on the pop, dance, R&B, and visual media fields.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.grammy.com/artist/justin-timberlake|title = Justin Timberlake|date = |accessdate = |website = Grammy.com|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> 8 nominations as part of [[NSYNC]] are counted. Two of Timberlake's studio albums have been nominated for [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]] so far: ''[[Justified (album)|Justified]]'' in 2004, and ''[[FutureSex/LoveSounds]]'' in 2007.
