==Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association==
The [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association]] (WAFCA) is a group of [[film critics]] based out of [[Washington, D.C.]] that was founded in 2002. WAFCA is composed of nearly 50 DC-based [[film critics]] from [[television]], [[radio]], [[Printing|print]] and the [[internet]]. The group annually gives awards to the best in film as voted on by its members.

{{awards table}}
!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}
|-
|[[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Awards 2010|2010]]
|''[[The Social Network]]''
|[[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Award for Best Ensemble|Best Ensemble]]
|{{nom}}
| style="text-align:center;"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dcfilmcritics.com/awards/ |title=The 2012 WAFCA Awards |work=Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association|date=December 10, 2012 |accessdate=December 19, 2012}}</ref>
{{end}}

== World Music Awards ==
The [[World Music Awards]] is an international awards show founded in 1989 that annually honored [[recording artist]]s based on worldwide sales figures provided by the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] (IFPI). Justin Timberlake has won the award three times.

